      "name": "What is commercial finance in the UK?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Commercial finance refers to funding solutions used by businesses, including business loans, commercial mortgages, development finance and asset-backed lending."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the difference between commercial and residential finance?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Commercial finance is risk-priced and based on business performance or asset viability, whereas residential finance is income-based for individuals."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is commercial finance regulated?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Some areas are regulated, particularly where residential property or consumer elements are involved, but much commercial lending is unregulated."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does it take to arrange a commercial finance?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "It varies by product. Unsecured loans may complete in days, while property-backed transactions can take several weeks."
      }
    }
  ]
}

